   </info>
   <refnamediv>
       <refname>sortc</refname>
               <refpurpose>mimics gauss function sortc </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[matout]=sortc(matin,val)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> matin </term> =    input (nxp) matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> val </term> =    value to fill the holes</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> matout </term> =    (nxp) transformed matrix</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Function that mimics gauss function sortc: sorts a matrix according to the value of one of its columns 

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
A=[1 3 2 4; 5 1 0 2 ; 4 2 1 2];B=sortc(A,3)// returns
// B  =//!   5.    1.    0.    2. !//!   4.    2.    1.    2. !//!   1.    3.    2.    4. !
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
